er  headquarters dublin ireland key people nicky hartery chairman albert manifold ceo products cement aggregates readymixed concrete asphaltbitumen and agricultural andor chemical lime revenue € million  operating income € million  net income € million  number of employees   website wwwcrhie crh plc is the parent company for an international group of diversified building materials businesses which are engaged in the manufacture and supply of a wide range of building materials and in the operation of builders’ merchanting and diy stores the company is incorporated and domiciled in ireland where it ranks as the largest irish company crh has a primary listing on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index it has secondary listings on the irish stock exchange where it is a constituent of the iseq  and new york stock exchange contents  history  s formation and listings  s early europe and us acquisitions   later acquisitions   americas and emerging markets  governance and operating structure  headquarters and board  structure and divisions  financial performance  controversy  cartel accusations  poland  ireland  united states  allegations of corrupt payments to politicians  poland  ireland  illegal ansbacher bank  sale of glen ding lands  public criticism  see also  references  external links historyedit s formation and listingsedit the company whose name is an abbreviation of cement roadstone holdings was formed through the merger in  of cement ltd established in  and roadstone ltd established in  according to jonathan guthrie of the financial times it is pronounced “cee orr haitch” the company went public on the irish stock exchange in  crh entered the united states in  by buying amcor a concrete products group in utah which would then form the basis of the companys us division which is now called oldcastle inc subsequent large purchases in the us included callanan industries a new york state based aggregates and asphalt producer in  in  crh was listed on londons ftse  index s early europe and us acquisitionsedit in the s the company moved into france with a number of buys including raboni sa a builders merchant company and drainage systems and concrete vault manufacturing group prefaest sa in  crh made its first entry into new or emerging markets when it bought holding cement polski which later gained majority control of cementownia ozarow one of the polands major cement producers that acquisition also marked the first crh cement manufacturing operation outside ireland by the end of the decade crh numbered more than a dozen operations in poland and it has since invested in cement production in neighbouring ukraine most recently with the announcement of an agreement to buy mykolaiv cement from rival lafarge in  crh bought finnsementti oy finlands only cement producer and lohja rudus oy finlands countrys top producer of aggregates and readymix concrete in the s us acquisitions by crh included betco block  products inc of bethesda maryland in  crh acquired balf co in connecticut lebanon rock in pennsylvania keating in massachusetts and sullivan lafarge in new york state in  it acquired allied building products which specialized in roofing and cladding products and tilcon a major road construction specialist in the northeast united states in   later acquisitionsedit crh global production sites in  the company entered switzerland in  with the eur  million purchase of jura group adding cement concrete and aggregates operations as well as a regional distribution network in the following year crh took an interest in nesher israel cement works the only cement producer in that country by taking a  stake in its holding company mashav in july  it agreed to pay eur  million to acquire cementbouw  a marketleading doityourself store chain and building materials producer in the netherlands in  crh paid €m to purchase a  percent stake in portuguese cement producer secil it sold that stake again in  for €m following a ruling on a shareholder dispute by an arbitration tribunal at the parisbased international chamber of commerce  in the united states crh also acquired ohios shelly group in  and crh acquired mount hope rock products based in new jersey in  and ashland paving and construction apac of atlanta in  apac was the companys largest ever deal in  crh purchased four companies worth a total of  million € million to add to its us materials division these companies are conrad yelvington distributors inc cydi eugene sand  gravel cessford construction and mcminns asphalt and prospect agrregates also in  crh agreed to purchase a landscape paver pavestone for  million in  crh took a new turn and invested in a cement factory based in the heilongjiang region in china it has built on that presence acquiring a  stake in the jilin yatai group and an option to acquire  in the future in  crh agreed to buy a  percent stake in indian cement company my home industries ltd for € million  million  americas and emerging marketsedit cement transport wagon of the french subsidiary eqiom crh confirmed in  that it was interested in looking at other opportunities in india n  crh remained listed in both london and dublin in february  crh agreed to purchase the uk building materials producer lafarge tarmac in  crh purchased us  billion of assets from the newly formed company lafargeholcim the acquisition almost tripled crhs net debt bringing it to € billion the lafargeholcim acquisition made crh the world’s thirdlargest building materials group by market value a week after ceo albert manifold announced that crh was looking for largescale acquisitions in august  crh paid  billion for cr laurence a glazing company based in california at the time crh already had a similar business in north america called buildingenvelope with  employees which it said it would integrate with crl by november  crh was getting about a fifth of its operating earnings from us infrastructure in june  the financial times reported that 