sitions by crh included betco block  products inc of bethesda maryland in  crh acquired balf co in connecticut lebanon rock in pennsylvania keating in massachusetts and sullivan lafarge in new york state in  it acquired allied building products which specialized in roofing and cladding products and tilcon a major road construction specialist in the northeast united states in   later acquisitionsedit crh global production sites in  the company entered switzerland in  with the eur  million purchase of jura group adding cement concrete and aggregates operations as well as a regional distribution network in the following year crh took an interest in nesher israel cement works the only cement producer in that country by taking a  stake in its holding company mashav in july  it agreed to pay eur  million to acquire cementbouw  a marketleading doityourself store chain and building materials producer in the netherlands in  crh paid €m to purchase a  percent stake in portuguese cement producer secil it sold that stake again in  for €m following a ruling on a shareholder dispute by an arbitration tribunal at the parisbased international chamber of commerce  in the united states crh also acquired ohios shelly group in  and crh acquired mount hope rock products based in new jersey in  and ashland paving and construction apac of atlanta in  apac was the companys largest ever deal in  crh purchased four companies worth a total of  million € million to add to its us materials division these companies are conrad yelvington distributors inc cydi eugene sand  gravel cessford construction and mcminns asphalt and prospect agrregates also in  crh agreed to purchase a landscape paver pavestone for  million in  crh took a new turn and invested in a cement factory based in the heilongjiang region in china it has built on that presence acquiring a  stake in the jilin yatai group and an option to acquire  in the future in  crh agreed to buy a  percent stake in indian cement company my home industries ltd for € million  million  americas and emerging marketsedit cement transport wagon of the french subsidiary eqiom crh confirmed in  that it was interested in looking at other opportunities in india n  crh remained listed in both london and dublin in february  crh agreed to purchase the uk building materials producer lafarge tarmac in  crh purchased us  billion of assets from the newly formed company lafargeholcim the acquisition almost tripled crhs net debt bringing it to € billion the lafargeholcim acquisition made crh the world’s thirdlargest building materials group by market value a week after ceo albert manifold announced that crh was looking for largescale acquisitions in august  crh paid  billion for cr laurence a glazing company based in california at the time crh already had a similar business in north america called buildingenvelope with  employees which it said it would integrate with crl by november  crh was getting about a fifth of its operating earnings from us infrastructure in june  the financial times reported that crh earned twice as much profit from the americas versus europe as of november  half the asphalt aggregates and assorted material it sold went to the united states headquartered in dublin crh was also the biggest producer of asphalt in the us and the third largest producer of readymixed concrete sales for  were € billion an increase of  percent from the year before profit after tax was € billion in april  the irish times noted that chief executive albert manifold’s package almost doubled in  to € million despite disagreement among shareholders the year before on pay as of april   crh was irelands biggest company chief executive was albert manifold that quarter sales were up in its three divisions in europe while the americas materials unit had higher sales as well at the time it did  percent of its business in the americas while the market in the philippines proving to be challenging and weighing down performance in asia on april   crh held their annual general meeting in dublin at which point  percent of shareholders voted against the companys executive pay structure the year prior  percent had voted against at the meeting chairman nick hartery noted that share price in the company had increased  percent since  also in april  it was reported that crh was expecting to make a largescale acquisition in  at the time over the earlier part of the year crh had spent € million on eight acquisitions in early may  blackrock increased its stake in crh plc governance and operating structureedit headquarters and boardedit crh is registered in ireland and headquartered in dublin ireland it has a board of  members three directors are executives of the group albert manifold chief executive ireland senan murphy group finance director ireland maeve carton group transformation director ireland each of the nine remaining sits as a nonexecutive director nicky hartery chairman ireland ernst bärtschi switzerland patrick kennedy ireland heather ann mcsharry ireland gillian platt canada lucinda riches uk henk rottinghuis netherlands willian teuber us donald a mcgovern jr senior independent director us mark towe chairman crh americas retired from the plc board on  december  structure and divisionsedit the crh business today is structured into four activities heavyside materials heavyside products lightside products distribution among the divisions are oldcastle inc financial performanceedit the following is a summary of financial data €m              revenue              ebitda              depreciation              amortisation              ebit              profit on disposals              profit before finance costs              finance costs net              associates              profit before tax              income tax              profit after tax              controversyedit cartel accusationsedit polandedit in poland in  crh was fined € by the polish competition and consumer protection commission for interfering with evidence that polish authorities were gathering for a pricefixing investigation in  grupa ożarów in which crh first invested in  was fined € million for operating a price fixing cartel in poland the polish competition regulator stated that seven companies which accounted for almost  per cent of the market had fixed minimum prices for grey cement and agreed on a market share for each operator crh has stated its belief that ozarów operated an independent commercial policy in poland and the fine has been appealed irelandedit in ireland in  irish cement limited a wholly owned subsidiary of crh was determined by the european commission to be part of price fixing and market sharing cartel across europe which it said had illegally and artificially inflated the price of cement throughout the continent a fine of over € million was levied two years later in ireland also in  high court proceedings were initiated against crh its subsidiaries and two competitors in which the plaintiffs accused crh and the others of operating a cartel and employing an illegal and anticompetitive eviction strategy in order to put them out of business in  crh applied successfully to have the claim dismissed on the basis of the inordinate and inexcusable delay in bringing forward any evidence in the case that judgement was appealed to the supreme court in  at the time of the appeal it emerged that the presiding judge in the proceedings had ownership of some shares in crh and was forced to stand down in  a separate irish high court action was initiated against crh by another company who claimed crh operated a cartel and abused a position of dominance in order to evict it from the marketcitation needed as of  the irish cement and concrete industry at large was under investigation by the irish competition authority united statesedit in  an antitrust lawsuit was filed in california against oldcastle precast crh subsidiary and three att affiliates the defendants were alleged to have unreasonably restrained trade and conspired to monopolize telephone vaults for landline connections plaintiffs challenged a contract requiring developers to purchase oldcastle precast product for properties served by att infrastructure they also contended the arrangement led to oldcastle precast capturing northern california sales of precast electrical vaults which were often placed concurrently with telephone structures in  an american court of appeal ruled that the plaintiff’s counsel had failed to provide enough evidence to show that the defendants oldcastle precast inc and three att affiliates harmed competition in california and nevada telephone vault markets in october  a cement and concrete price fixing class action lawsuit was filed in florida against oldcastle materials crh subsidiary and others the claim alleged that the defendants eliminated competition in the market for cement and concrete by charging artificially high prices from at least the period  to  the claim further alleged that the conspiracy was facilitated through inpersonal meetings telephone conversations and other communications in  the defendants announced uniform price increases for concrete and cement bringing their prices to the same level at the same time the lawsuit claimed then in september a number of defendant companies cut the price of concrete in an effort to lure customers away from independently owned concrete firms the lawsuit stated that the practices alleged in the cement and concrete industry were clearly illegal in  the case was settled for undisclosed terms the largest cases in the usa seem to be in florida  to   price fixing  new jersey for blowing up a mine in context of federal grant money potential frauds however the grandiose doings near lake deforest in new city  dutchtown  haverstraw and west nyack ny since about  to  are shocking but not surprising one may obtain the latest consent orders by calling the new region  director kelly turturro at  and the dec can put you in contact with eric kim of the dow branch of the dec for details about unpaid fines regarding testinganalysis that seems not to be viably done for many years also in consent orders  last quarter  dec authored haverstraw quarry notice of violation dated nov   to some extent allegations of corrupt payments to politiciansedit polandedit in  a polish businessman marek dochnal alleged to a polish parliamentary inquiry that he had arranged a bribe of almost  million for crh to a former minister for privatisation wieslaw kaczmarek in connection with the privatisation of a cement plant at ozarow in central poland in  crh which now owns and operates the cement plant at ozarow said the allegations were without foundation it was also revealed in  that crh contributed € to a charity founded by the wife of poland’s president jolanta kwasniewska both crh and the polish first lady denied any sinister motive behind the transaction irelandedit in  crh was accused of making corrupt payments to ireland’s former taoiseach prime minister charles j haughey as details emerged of how mr haughey received crooked payments from various companies and businessmen in return for political favours in  roadstone ltd crh sold  acres of land to mr haughey the then minister of finance for £ in  mr haughey sold  acres of that land back to crh for £ within four years mr haughey had made a net profit of £ and  acres at crh’s expense charles j haughey was also offered chairmanship of crh in  illegal ansbacher bankedit the existence of a clandestine bank illegally providing off shore accounts first emerged in  during the mccracken tribunal set up to investigate reports of secret payments to corrupt former taoiseach irish prime minister charles haughey and former cabinet minister michael lowry it emerged this illegal bank was founded in the s and was being run by des traynor who was chairman of crh from  to  and who ran his bank during that period out of crh’s registered office in dublins fitzwilliam square where the company provided an office for its chairman mr traynor was also personal financier to charles haughey during the investigation it materialised that justice moriarty held approximately £ in crh shares and while that in his opinion precluded him from investigating certain matters concerning crh he was not he said precluded from inquiring into banking activities conducted from des traynors offices at fitzwilliam square sharp criticism was laid upon those in charge of appointing moriarty given his shareholding in  as evidence on the scale of the ansbacher accounts grew taniste irish deputy prime minister and pd minister mary harney asked the high court to appoint inspectors who could identify the account holders the high court inspectors report was published in  it found that eight out of fifteen crh directors held ansbacher accounts including four former chairmen it also concluded chapter  p  that crh as a corporation cannot be said to have knowingly assisted in the carrying out of ansbacher’s activities in ireland after the publication of the report crh acknowledged publicly that its then chairman had misused its facilities and personnel which represented a grave breach of trust by mr traynor sale of glen ding landsedit in  further questions were asked about crh’s influence and political corruption when dáil éireann ireland’s parliament voted against an investigation into why an asset with the potential to produce a yield of £ million in terms of sand and gravel reserves was sold to roadstone a subsidiary company of crh without public tender for £ million in  many opposition members of parliament voiced concerns that at the time of sale charles j haughey was taoiseach and his financier des traynor was chairman of crh dáil éireann however voted not to investigate whether crh had donated funds to any political party or politician before or after the purchase of glen ding subsequently corrupt findings in unrelated matters have been made against a number of those who voted against the investigation the states comptroller and auditor general conducted an investigation into the sale and found that the competing bid fell far short of the roadstone offer and that the department acted at all times in the best commercial interests of the state section  it did also note even though it is unlikely that the roadstone offer would have been bettered the attraction of concluding the sale at what was considered a good price outweighed the imperative to act evenhandedly which is a basic principle when the state is doing business it was noted by the departments accounting officer that the roadstone offer was more than  above the only alternative offer received that another bidder was afforded every opportunity to make a better offer and that given subsequent delays and planning issues in retrospect the deal had proved to be exceptional the glen ding transaction was further investigated by the moriarty tribunal which in  reported its conclusion that there was no connection directly or indirectly between mr charles haughey and any aspect of this disposal nor any connection between the operation of the ansbacher accounts and any aspect of the disposal public criticismedit in  opposition td teachta dála  irish member of parliament phil hogan who later became minister for environment    stated in dáil éireann that there is a widespread problem with competition in this economy………in the case of crh profits have been extracted from the irish economy by means of a complex industry structure that is both anticompetitive and anticonsumer the european court of first instance and finally the european court of justice have upheld findings of serious anticompetitive behaviour against crh and other while sweden finland uk france and germany have since levied huge fines against the cement industry ireland’s answer has been a stony silence in  td shane ross a repeated critic of crh as a journalist stated that crh disturbs him and questioned why there had been no investigation of crh in ireland considering the adverse findings made against the company elsewhere see alsoedit the major international materials groups that would be comparable to crh include cemex mexico heidelbergcement germany holcim switzerland italcementi italy lafarge france saintgobain france wolseley uk martin marietta materials us vulcan materials company us list of irish companies referencesedit  a b c preliminary results  pdf crh plc retrieved  april    our group crh plc retrieved  april    crh on topie irish times   crh history overview crhcom retrieved  march    guthrie jonathan august   crh options not manifold in a downturn financial times retrieved may     crh plc irish stock exchange retrieved  march    callanan industries purchased by oldcastle inc callanancom  a b c d duffy sean april   the irish independent ireland httpwwwindependentiebusinesscrhfacespushbackovermforceohtml retrieved may    missing or empty title help  crh buys french builders merchants europolitics  october   crh raises holding in polish firm to pc irish independent  october   international cement review crh invests €m in its ukraine cement plant cemnetcom retrieved  march    crh buys ukrainian cement firm for €m from rival irish independent  april   scancem sells finnsementti and lohja rudus operations to crh news powered by cision retrieved  march    irish building materials giant buys bethesda masonry firm washington business journal   february   crh buys four us businesses for m ft  uk company news  august   allied products bought by crh new york times  july   crh bolts on swiss firm in £m deal irish independent  november   dublins crh buys mashav stake the daily deal   august   cvc sells cementbouw to crh for €m dow jones efinancial news  july   crh gets windfall of €m as portuguese firm buys out stake irish independent  april   crh acquires major materials business in ohio pr newsire  february   crhs oldcastle group buys new jersey quarry firm rtéie  april  retri